{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"`PointsMaterial.size` has units of pixels -- not world units. You will have to adjust the size yourself.\r\n\r\nThis related post may be informative: https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10385#issuecomment-267789138.\r\n\r\nBeware that `gl_PointSize` may be limited, so the size you request may not be the size you get.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-09-07T16:31:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12150#issuecomment-327853358","id":327853358,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12150","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMyNzg1MzM1OA==","updated_at":"2017-09-07T16:31:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/327853358","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley. So I need to change the size property of the PointsMaterial when I change the FOV?\r\n\r\nI did find that post before asking but I don't quite follow why it works that way. I understand that size is in pixels but attenuation already makes it not relate to devices pixels and that process surely must relate to perspective which must relate to FOV in some sense?\r\n\r\nHowever, that's just explaining my own lack of understanding. I'm perfectly happy with the solution you give. Thanks.","created_at":"2017-09-07T16:50:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12150#issuecomment-327858701","id":327858701,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12150","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMyNzg1ODcwMQ==","updated_at":"2017-09-07T16:50:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/327858701","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12849146?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/orangebowlerhat","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyODQ5MTQ2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/orangebowlerhat\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/a